it is by thinking

00:02:56.820 --> 00:03:00.490 align:middle line:84%
about these things that
helps us to navigate

00:03:00.490 --> 00:03:02.660 align:middle line:90%
the extremes in our lives.

00:03:02.660 --> 00:03:05.750 align:middle line:84%
And the fact is, the world
of the past no longer exists.

00:03:05.750 --> 00:03:09.230 align:middle line:84%
A new normal is
emerging, and many people

00:03:09.230 --> 00:03:14.090 align:middle line:84%
are clinging to an idea of
what the old world looks like,

00:03:14.090 --> 00:03:16.052 align:middle line:84%
waiting for things
to get back to normal

00:03:16.052 --> 00:03:18.260 align:middle line:84%
rather than embracing the
opportunities of right now.

00:03:18.260 --> 00:03:19.600 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I'm
excited to talk to you.

00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:20.099 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

